  "texts": [
    "A second pattern is traditional-tool-guided generation, where the outputs of traditional tools provide structured feedback to LLMs.",
    "For instance, surviving mutants from mutation testing tools can be fed back to LLMs, explicitly guiding them to generate stronger, more fault-revealing tests [32].",
    "We believe future work should focus on creating general hybrid frameworks that formalize these integration patterns, thereby achieving a \"1+1>2\" effect.Synergy with Human Expertise.",
    "Addressing the challenges of poor maintainability and the need to root test generation in high-level intent, which LLMs struggle to infer in isolation, has given rise to a paradigm where human expertise is augmented rather than replaced.",
    "This opportunity stems from the recognition that full automation is not always the most effective or desirable goal; instead, empowering human developers can lead to higher productivity and quality."
  ],
